 <item> <title>Critical NASA Science Returns to Earth aboard SpaceX Dragon Spacecraft</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/critical-nasa-science-returns-to-earth-aboard-spacex-dragon-spacecraft</link>
 <description>A SpaceX Dragon cargo spacecraft splashed down in the Pacific Ocean at 2:51 p.m. EDT Wednesday, May 11, about 261 miles southwest of Long Beach, California, with more than 3,700 pounds of NASA cargo, science and technology demonstration samples from the International Space Station.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/675b8385.jpeg?itok=-i3NIGIp" length="5029075" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/critical-nasa-science-returns-to-earth-aboard-spacex-dragon-spacecraft</guid>
 <pubDate>Wed, 11 May 2016 15:00 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA's Kepler Mission Announces Largest Collection of Planets Ever Discovered</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasas-kepler-mission-announces-largest-collection-of-planets-ever-discovered</link>
 <description>NASA's Kepler mission has verified 1,284 new planets – the single largest finding of planets to date.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/kepler_all-planets_may2016.jpg?itok=9PMyOJ5p" length="2829984" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasas-kepler-mission-announces-largest-collection-of-planets-ever-discovered</guid>
 <pubDate>Tue, 10 May 2016 13:10 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA, Space Station Partners Announce Future Mission Crew Members</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-space-station-partners-announce-future-mission-crew-members</link>
 <description>NASA and its International Space Station partners have announced the crew members for missions to the orbiting laboratory in 2017. The selection includes first-time space flyer NASA astronaut Scott Tingle and veteran Randy Bresnik.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/s135e011864.jpg?itok=bhcg3a1g" length="778009" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-space-station-partners-announce-future-mission-crew-members</guid>
 <pubDate>Fri, 06 May 2016 11:11 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA TV to Broadcast Dragon Departure from International Space Station</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-tv-to-broadcast-dragon-departure-from-international-space-station</link>
 <description>After delivering almost 7,000 pounds of cargo to the International Space Station, including the Bigelow Expandable Activity Module (BEAM), the SpaceX Dragon cargo spacecraft is set to leave the orbital laboratory with valuable science research and return to Earth on Wednesday, May 11. NASA Television will provide live coverage of Dragon's departure</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/dragon-crs8.jpg?itok=eulXq6GW" length="1976929" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-tv-to-broadcast-dragon-departure-from-international-space-station</guid>
 <pubDate>Thu, 05 May 2016 16:33 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA Makes Dozens of Patents Available in Public Domain to Benefit U.S. Industry</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-makes-dozens-of-patents-available-in-public-domain-to-benefit-us-industry</link>
 <description>NASA has released 56 formerly-patented agency technologies into the public domain, making its government-developed technologies freely available for unrestricted commercial use. In addition to the release of these technologies, a searchable database now is available that catalogues thousands of expired NASA patents already in the public domain.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/public_domain_box.2.png?itok=Qokt_c02" length="191858" type="image/png" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-makes-dozens-of-patents-available-in-public-domain-to-benefit-us-industry</guid>
 <pubDate>Thu, 05 May 2016 16:00 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA to Announce Latest Kepler Discoveries During Media Teleconference</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-announce-latest-kepler-discoveries-during-media-teleconference</link>
 <description>NASA will host a news teleconference at 1 p.m. EDT Tuesday, May 10 to announce the latest discoveries made by its planet-hunting mission, the Kepler Space Telescope.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/lithoartkepler2-full.jpg?itok=8xkNdCND" length="370256" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-announce-latest-kepler-discoveries-during-media-teleconference</guid>
 <pubDate>Wed, 04 May 2016 14:49 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA to Provide Coverage of May 9 Mercury Transit of the Sun</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-provide-coverage-of-may-9-mercury-transit-of-the-sun</link>
 <description>NASA is inviting media and viewers around the world to see a relatively rare celestial event, with coverage of the Monday, May 9 transit of the sun by the planet Mercury. Media may view the event at NASA’s Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/m16-050.jpg?itok=wLlYOLUF" length="361300" type="image/jpeg" />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-provide-coverage-of-may-9-mercury-transit-of-the-sun</guid>
 <pubDate>Tue, 03 May 2016 10:10 EDT</pubDate>
 <source url="http://www.nasa.gov/rss/dyn/breaking_news.rss">NASA Breaking News</source>
</item>
 <item> <title>NASA Welcomes New Director for its Jet Propulsion Laboratory</title>

 <description>The following is a statement from NASA Administrator Charles Bolden on the selection of Michael Watkins as the new director of the agency’s Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL) in Pasadena, California.</description>

 <item> <title>NASA Awards Contract for Aeronautics, Exploration Modeling, Simulation</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-awards-contract-for-aeronautics-exploration-modeling-simulation</link>
 <description>NASA has selected Science and Technology Corporation of Hampton, Virginia, to provide support services at the agency’s Ames Research Center, Moffett Field, California under the Aeronautics and Exploration Mission Modeling and Simulation (AEMMS) contract.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/nasa-logo-web-rgb.jpg?itok=L07ZQKnk" length="189751" type="image/jpeg" />

 <item> <title>NASA Astronauts to Call Chicago Area Students from International Space Station</title>
 <link>http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-astronauts-to-call-chicago-area-students-from-international-space-station</link>
 <description>Students from 11 schools in South Holland, Illinois, will have the opportunity to speak with two NASA astronauts currently living and working aboard the International Space Station at 11:55 a.m. EDT Thursday, May 5. The 20-minute, Earth-to-space call will air live on NASA Television and the agency’s website.</description>
 <enclosure url="http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/1x1_cardfeed/public/thumbnails/image/128e5960.jpg?itok=Abu27Go7" length="2294921" type="image/jpeg" />
